Date: Thu, 2 Feb 2017 17:16:11 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1720/2066] mmc: sh_mobile_sdhi: Add bus_shift according to
 register arrangement

Deleted by revert of "mmc: sh_mobile_sdhi: Add r8a7795 support",
but this patch's processing is necessary.

Signed-off-by: Masaharu Hayakawa <masaharu.hayakawa.ry@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c |    7 +++++--
 1 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c b/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c
index 2e1b1a3..5673f26 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@
  * SuperH Mobile SDHI
  *
  * Copyright (C) 2016 Sang Engineering, Wolfram Sang
- * Copyright (C) 2015-16 Renesas Electronics Corporation
+ * Copyright (C) 2015-2017 Renesas Electronics Corporation
  * Copyright (C) 2009 Magnus Damm
  *
  * This program is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify
@@ -728,7 +728,10 @@ static int sh_mobile_sdhi_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	}
 
 	/* Orginally registers were 16 bit apart, could be 32 or 64 nowadays */
-	if (!host->bus_shift && resource_size(res) > 0x100) /* old way to determine the shift */
+	if (resource_size(res) > 0x400)
+		host->bus_shift = 2;
+	else if (!host->bus_shift &&
+	    resource_size(res) > 0x100) /* old way to determine the shift */
 		host->bus_shift = 1;
 
 	if (mmd)
